modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and serializing WAMP protocol messages, including handling of tuples, lists, and binary data. Implements message encoding and decoding for events, publications, and procedure calls. Used to facilitate real-time communication in distributed systems requiring bidirectional message exchange.

Converts between message type enums and values, and generates WAMP protocol messages for communication over WebSockets. Works with URIs, dictionaries, and message structures to handle session initiation, event publishing, subscription management, and error reporting. Constructs messages for hello, welcome, publish, subscribe, event delivery, and termination scenarios in real-time applications.
